definitions.definition: Each of the lymphatic vessels which convey chyle from the mesentery to the thoracic duct.
One of the lactiferous ducts or other components of milk-producing organs.

main_definition: ( physiology , chiefly in the plural ) Each of the lymphatic vessels which convey chyle from the mesentery to the thoracic duct.
secondary_definitions: ( obsolete ) One of the lactiferous ducts or other components of milk-producing organs.
